              The heat maps tell you everything you need to know about how dominant a performance this was for Spurs, in possession and territory at least. Swansea, to be fair, defended well. The crossbar and an inspired performance from an underrated goalkeeper prevented that from happening. Not the first of this season and not the last I suspect.
